Definition: Date the ARMS unit was deployed
Date the ARMS unit was collected
The ID of the replicate field that this unit is part of
The filtered fraction of the material sample

The preservative used: ETOH or DMSO (see the ARMS Handbook for details; note that the preservative could be DMSO or DMSO-EDTA-NaCl, i.e. DESS, this distinction was not tracked for these sampling events). For events in 2018 and 2019 both where used, thereafter only DMSO
Material sample ID with _r1 (technical replicate 1) or _r2 (technical replicate 2) appended
As sequencing runs were sometimes repeated, but previous runs retained, this contains the repeat value (first, second, etc) of the run
Information about why sequencing was repeated (where relevant)
The pore size of the filter (lower limit; material larger than this is collected)
Was a crate cover used during retrieval of the unit
Number of images associated with this event
The gene types for which sequences are available in ENA
